---
layout: post
title:  "Liz and Simon plan a move, Bryn's given an unpleasant diagnosis, Fiona takes a long walk, and Kit helps her fix a tent"
date:   2013-09-09 11:01:56
---

![Fiona with a pack of golden retreivers](http://fionafish.files.wordpress.com/2013/09/bute-13-101.jpg?w=650)

[Liz][liz] shared her and Simon's plans to sell their house in the North and [get a place together in the South](http://norasdollhouse.livejournal.com/114646.html), after eighteen months of running their relationship long-distance.

[Bryn][bryn] was diagnosed with [Sharp's syndrome](http://randomlyevil.org.uk/2013/09/03/turning-to-health-news/), a rare autoimmune disease without a cure.

[Fiona][fiona] walked the West Island Way, [to Port Bannatyne](http://fionafish.wordpress.com/2013/09/02/west-island-way/), [via Kames Bay](http://fionafish.wordpress.com/2013/09/03/ettrick-bay-to-rhubodach-2/), [round Kilchattan Bay](http://fionafish.wordpress.com/2013/09/04/kilchattan-bay-circular/), and [back](http://fionafish.wordpress.com/2013/09/05/the-last-leg/). Returning home, she and [Kit][kit] continued their effort to [repair a tent](http://fionafish.wordpress.com/2013/09/06/tent-repairs-part-2/).

